HEADWORD: Hommock
<hw>Hom"mock</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A small eminence of a
conical form, of land or of ice; a knoll; a hillock. See
<er>Hummock</er>.</def> <rj><au>Bartram.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hommocky</ent>⟦br⟧
